Because triangle $ABC$ is similar to triangle $XYZ,$ $\frac{AB}{XY}=\frac{BC}{YZ}.$ Plugging in the values we are given yields \begin{align*}
\frac{4}{14} &= \frac{6}{YZ}\\
\Rightarrow\qquad \frac{4\cdot YZ}{14} &= 6\\
\Rightarrow\qquad 4\cdot YZ &= 84\\
\Rightarrow\qquad YZ &= \boxed{21}.
\end{align*}
